  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-02 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across five flow-speed combinations. Thirteen credibility factors were assessed; the majority achieved required levels. Two factors — Discretization error and Model form — were assessed at levels below their required thresholds due to mesh-refinement resource constraints and constitutive-model limitations acknowledged during review. The assessment team concluded that compensating controls and conservative hemolysis thresholds provide adequate assurance for regulatory submission.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-absolute-threshold",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cou2-hemolysis-below-clinical-limit",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-centrifugal-pump-hemolysis-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-measurements-2023",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/hemolysis-bench-test-5conditions"
  ],
  "hasContextOfUse": {
    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to predict absolute hemolysis levels across operating conditions for a centrifugal blood pump used as a ventricular assist device (VAD). Model influence is HIGH (model is primary basis for hemolysis acceptance); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect prediction could result in chronic patient hemolysis requiring clinical intervention). Model Risk Level 5 — the highest in the Morrison assessment.",
    "deviceClass": "Class III",
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou2-vad",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to predict absolute hemolysis index values for a Class III VAD device across 5 flow-speed combinations. Results must demonstrate hemolysis below absolute clinical threshold (not relative to predicate). Requires Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on hemolysis predictions.",
    "modelInfluence": "High",
    "name": "COU2: Ventricular assist device use (Class III)",
    "type": "ContextOfUse"
  },
